15221 #if FF_CODE_PAGE != 0 && FF_CODE_PAGE < 900
15222 WCHAR ff_uni2oem ( /* Returns OEM code character, zero on error */
15223  DWORD uni, /* UTF-16 encoded character to be converted */
15224  WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15225 )
15226 {
15227  WCHAR c = 0;
15228  const WCHAR *p = CVTBL(uc, FF_CODE_PAGE);
15229 
15230 
15231  if (uni < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15232  c = (WCHAR)uni;
15233 
15234  } else { /* Non-ASCII */
15235  if (uni < 0x10000 && cp == FF_CODE_PAGE) { /* Is it in BMP and valid code page? */
15236  for (c = 0; c < 0x80 && uni != p[c]; c++) ;
15237  c = (c + 0x80) & 0xFF;
15238  }
15239  }
15240 
15241  return c;
15242 }

15251 
15252

15254  c = oem;
15255 
15256  } else { /* Extended char */

15258  if (oem < 0x100) c = p[oem - 0x80];
15259  }
15260  }

15274 #if FF_CODE_PAGE >= 900
15275 WCHAR ff_uni2oem ( /* Returns OEM code character, zero on error */
15276  DWORD uni, /* UTF-16 encoded character to be converted */
15277  WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15278 )
15279 {
15280  const WCHAR *p;
15281  WCHAR c = 0, uc;
15282  UINT i = 0, n, li, hi;
15283 
15284 
15285  if (uni < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15286  c = (WCHAR)uni;
15287 
15288  } else { /* Non-ASCII */
15289  if (uni < 0x10000 && cp == FF_CODE_PAGE) { /* Is it in BMP and valid code page? */
15290  uc = (WCHAR)uni;
15291  p = CVTBL(uni2oem, FF_CODE_PAGE);
15292  hi = sizeof CVTBL(uni2oem, FF_CODE_PAGE) / 4 - 1;
15293  li = 0;
15294  for (n = 16; n; n--) {
15295  i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
15296  if (uc == p[i * 2]) break;
15297  if (uc > p[i * 2]) {
15298  li = i;
15299  } else {
15300  hi = i;
15301  }
15302  }
15303  if (n != 0) c = p[i * 2 + 1];
15304  }
15305  }
15306 
15307  return c;
15308 }

15358 WCHAR ff_uni2oem ( /* Returns OEM code character, zero on error */
15359  DWORD uni, /* UTF-16 encoded character to be converted */
15360  WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15361 )
15362 {
15363  const WCHAR *p;
15364  WCHAR c = 0, uc;
15365  UINT i, n, li, hi;
15366 
15367 
15368  if (uni < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15369  c = (WCHAR)uni;
15370 
15371  } else { /* Non-ASCII */
15372  if (uni < 0x10000) { /* Is it in BMP? */
15373  uc = (WCHAR)uni;
15374  p = 0;
15375  if (cp < 900) { /* SBCS */
15376  for (i = 0; cp_code[i] != 0 && cp_code[i] != cp; i++) ; /* Get conversion table */
15377  p = cp_table[i];
15378  if (p) { /* Is it valid code page ? */
15379  for (c = 0; c < 0x80 && uc != p[c]; c++) ; /* Find OEM code in the table */
15380  c = (c + 0x80) & 0xFF;
15381  }
15382  } else { /* DBCS */
15383  switch (cp) { /* Get conversion table */
15384  case 932 : p = uni2oem932; hi = sizeof uni2oem932 / 4 - 1; break;
15385  case 936 : p = uni2oem936; hi = sizeof uni2oem936 / 4 - 1; break;
15386  case 949 : p = uni2oem949; hi = sizeof uni2oem949 / 4 - 1; break;
15387  case 950 : p = uni2oem950; hi = sizeof uni2oem950 / 4 - 1; break;
15388  }
15389  if (p) { /* Is it valid code page? */
15390  li = 0;
15391  for (n = 16; n; n--) { /* Find OEM code */
15392  i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
15393  if (uc == p[i * 2]) break;
15394  if (uc > p[i * 2]) {
15395  li = i;
15396  } else {
15397  hi = i;
15398  }
15399  }
15400  if (n != 0) c = p[i * 2 + 1];
15401  }
15402  }
15403  }
15404  }
15405 
15406  return c;
15407 }

15410 WCHAR ff_oem2uni ( /* Returns Unicode character in UTF-16, zero on error */
15411  WCHAR oem, /* OEM code to be converted (DBC if >=0x100) */
15412  WORD cp /* Code page for the conversion */
15413 )
15414 {
15415  const WCHAR *p;
15416  WCHAR c = 0;
15417  UINT i, n, li, hi;
15418 
15419 
15420  if (oem < 0x80) { /* ASCII? */
15421  c = oem;
15422 
15423  } else { /* Extended char */
15424  p = 0;
15425  if (cp < 900) { /* SBCS */
15426  for (i = 0; cp_code[i] != 0 && cp_code[i] != cp; i++) ; /* Get table */
15427  p = cp_table[i];
15428  if (p) { /* Is it a valid CP ? */
15429  if (oem < 0x100) c = p[oem - 0x80];
15430  }
15431  } else { /* DBCS */
15432  switch (cp) {
15433  case 932 : p = oem2uni932; hi = sizeof oem2uni932 / 4 - 1; break;
15434  case 936 : p = oem2uni936; hi = sizeof oem2uni936 / 4 - 1; break;
15435  case 949 : p = oem2uni949; hi = sizeof oem2uni949 / 4 - 1; break;
15436  case 950 : p = oem2uni950; hi = sizeof oem2uni950 / 4 - 1; break;
15437  }
15438  if (p) {
15439  li = 0;
15440  for (n = 16; n; n--) {
15441  i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
15442  if (oem == p[i * 2]) break;
15443  if (oem > p[i * 2]) {
15444  li = i;
15445  } else {
15446  hi = i;
15447  }
15448  }
15449  if (n != 0) c = p[i * 2 + 1];
15450  }
15451  }
15452  }
15453 
15454  return c;
15455 }
